---
import ArticleLayout from '../../layouts/ArticleLayout.astro';

const locale = 'en';
---

<ArticleLayout
  title="Changelog"
  description="Release history for WorthCalc's free money-decision calculators."
  locale={locale}
  updated="2026-07-03"
>
  <h2>v1.0.0 - WorthCalc launch</h2>
  <p><time datetime="2026-07">July 2026</time></p>
  <p>
    First public release of WorthCalc, with eight free, browser-based
    calculators that answer one question: is it actually worth it?
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Installment True APR Calculator — the real interest rate behind "0%" installment and BNPL plans.</li>
    <li>Subscription Audit Calculator — total subscription cost per month, year, and 5 years.</li>
    <li>Costco Membership Calculator — break-even spend for Gold Star and Executive tiers.</li>
    <li>EV vs Gas Car TCO Calculator — total cost of ownership and break-even year.</li>
    <li>Rent vs Buy Calculator — mortgage, appreciation, and invested down payment vs. renting.</li>
    <li>Commute Cost Calculator — car, transit, rideshare, and bike compared side by side.</li>
    <li>Latte Factor Calculator — what a daily habit costs, and its future value if invested.</li>
    <li>Cashback Break-even Calculator — annual-fee card vs. a no-fee 1% baseline.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>
    Also included at launch: bilingual English and Traditional Chinese pages,
    four supporting guides on installments, subscriptions, warehouse-club math,
    and rent vs. buy, plus a fully client-side privacy model — no calculator
    input ever leaves your browser.
  </p>
</ArticleLayout>
